statement.p:
Let A=\mat{1 3 1 1; -1 -3 -4 2; 5 15 1 9}
What are \dim(\Nul A) and \dim((\Nul A)_{\perp})?
Find a basis for (\Nul A)_{\perp}.

ol.li:
Row reducing A yields: \mat{1 3 0 2; 0 0 1 -1;0 0 0 0} The variable x_2 and x_4 are free. The parametric form of the solution is:
\vec{x_1 x_2 x_3 x_4} = x_2\vec{-3 1 0 0} + x_4\vec{-2 0 1 1}
We can read off the null space from the parametric vector form; a basis is \bigl\{\vec{-3 1 0 0}, \vec{-2 0 1 1}\bigr\}. We can see that \dim(\Nul A) = 2. Since \Nul A is a subspace of \R^4, we have \dim((\Nul A)_{\perp})=4-\dim(\Nul A)=2.
